## 4. Download a prebuilt EMU database

EMU provides prebuilt databases through OSF. The default EMU database can be downloaded as `emu.tar`. Alternative databases include SILVA and SILVA 138.2.

### 4.1 Download the default EMU database

```bash
conda activate EMU
pip install osfclient

export EMU_DATABASE_DIR="$HOME/emu_databases/default_emu"
mkdir -p "$EMU_DATABASE_DIR"
cd "$EMU_DATABASE_DIR"

osf -p 56uf7 fetch osfstorage/emu-prebuilt/emu.tar
tar -xvf emu.tar
```

Expected files:

```text
species_taxid.fasta
taxonomy.tsv
```

### 4.2 Download the SILVA prebuilt database

```bash
conda activate EMU
pip install osfclient

export EMU_PREBUILT_DB="silva"
export EMU_DATABASE_DIR="$HOME/emu_databases/silva"
mkdir -p "$EMU_DATABASE_DIR"
cd "$EMU_DATABASE_DIR"

osf -p 56uf7 fetch osfstorage/emu-prebuilt/${EMU_PREBUILT_DB}.tar
tar -xvf ${EMU_PREBUILT_DB}.tar
```

Expected files may include:

```text
species_taxid.fasta
taxonomy.tsv
taxonomy_split.tsv
```
