## 8. Run EMU on short-read 16S data

For short-read data, use:

```bash
--type sr
```

EMU supports both single-end and paired-end short-read inputs.

---

### 8.1 Single-end short-read FASTQ

```bash
emu abundance sample_R1.fastq \
  --db "$HOME/emu_databases/eHOMD_EMU_DB" \
  --type sr \
  --output-dir short_read_outputs \
  --output-basename sample_R1 \
  --keep-counts \
  --min-abundance \
  --threads 16
```

---

### 8.2 Paired-end short-read FASTQ

```bash
emu abundance sample_R1.fastq sample_R2.fastq \
  --db "$HOME/emu_databases/eHOMD_EMU_DB" \
  --type sr \
  --output-dir short_read_outputs \
  --output-basename sample \
  --keep-counts \
  --min-abundance \
  --threads 16
```

---

### 8.3 Batch run for FASTA files

Use this if your short-read workflow produced dereplicated or processed `.fa` files.

```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -euo pipefail

BASE_DIR="$HOME/Finatag_derep_16S_SR"
OUTPUT_DIR="$BASE_DIR/Feces_oral"
DB_PATH="$HOME/emu_databases/eHOMD_EMU_DB"
THREADS=50

mkdir -p "$OUTPUT_DIR"

for fa in "$BASE_DIR"/*.fa; do

    sample=$(basename "$fa" .fa)
    echo "Processing $sample"

    emu abundance "$fa" \
        --db "$DB_PATH" \
        --type sr \
        --output-dir "$OUTPUT_DIR" \
        --output-basename "$sample" \
        --keep-files \
        --keep-counts \
        --keep-read-assignments \
        --output-unclassified \
        --min-abundance \
        --threads "$THREADS"

    echo "Finished $sample"

done
```

